# @purpose:      How does a user log in with a magic link?
# @audience:     Engineers new to the auth service
# @out-of-scope: Token rotation, rate limiting, error and abuse UX
# @tier:         governed
# @source:       (confected example — no upstream doc)

...@../../../references/style

user: User             { class: actor }
app:  Web App          { class: svc }
api:  Auth API         { class: svc }
mail: Email Provider   { class: external }
db:   Token Store      { class: store }

user -> app:  1. enter email
app  -> api:  2. request link
api  -> db:   3. store token
api  -> mail: 4. send link      { class: weak }
user -> app:  5. click link
app  -> api:  6. verify token
api  -> db:   7. check + consume
api  -> app:  8. issue session
